Skeletal arrangement: Choanosomic plurispicular fascicula of styles arranged in bunches near ectosome (
Fig. 9
). Ectosome consisting of irregularly arranged tangential styles with free exotyles or exotyles forming hispid bunches of 4 or 5 , with tyles pointing out. Cyrtancistras situated in ectosome underneath stylar layer. Very abundant sigmas arranged as ectosomal crust just beneath tangential styles.
